Deload and Get Low! Taking time to decrease weights can help clean up form, but also to make sure you're hitting those absolute positions. Weighted (Heavy) basketballs have been around for years, and have proven to be effective while being backed by the testimonials of players all around the world. Many think a weighted (heavy) ball is just for improving shooting range, which it does when executed properly (not what I suggest). But using a weighted (heavy) ball to improve dribbling, passing, catching, and rebounding is just as impactful, if not more! The weighted (heavy) basketball builds up the muscles in the arms, as well as strengthens the core, fingers and wrists. This leads to better grip on the ball and more control of the ball, as well as your own body. 

When you switch back to using a regulation basketball, you will immediately feel the difference in the quickness of your moves. This will also force you to control what is now a relatively much lighter ball. This initial feeling will gradually go away as you adjust back to the feel of the regular basketball.

Feel free to let me know which move(s) are your favorite 🙌🏾 [tag a friend] who you think would love this workout! 💪🏾

Don’t cut yourself short. 

First meet back off a foot injury and probably came back too soon. Gutted it out to finish my jump series, but I gave up on this jump thinking it wasn’t a great attempt after feeling major pain on the takeoff.

As you can see, that lazy right leg turned what might’ve been 7.6+ into a 7.14m. Lesson learned. No matter where you are, follow through on your attempts. Don’t cut yourself short. You might just surprise yourself. And as always, have fun with it 🤙🏾

Welcome to Couro! I’m Cam Van - Jumper, dog dad, CEO and co-Founder of Couro. We built Couro to be a platform built for athlete empowerment. 

Couro levels the playing field for athletes across the spectrum, creating a community where athletes, coaches, and trainers can curate their own exclusive content. Users can subscribe for access, receiving elite athletic insights, all while supporting their favorite athlete to achieve their dreams.

We’re working hard to make the best platform for all athletes, so as we do, please give us feedback on how we’re doing so we can shape the community into something that works for you!

I am a Sprinter training for the 2024 Olympics.

Join me on my journey, all are welcomed.
